            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>R. M. ROBINSON &#38; CO.<lb/>
                &#40;Successors to WM. G. MINTZER&#44;&#41;<lb/>
                Importers&#44; Manufacturers &#38; Furnishers of<lb/>
                Military&#44; Church&#44; Society&#44; Theatrical Goods&#44; &#38;c.<lb/>
                No. 131 North Third Street&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>R M. ROBINSON&#44;<lb/>
                CLARENCE A. HART.							Philadelphia&#44; Oct. 19 1870<lb/>
                Rev&#39;d&#58; S. Morais.<lb/>
                Dear Sir.<lb/></p>
            <p>Enclosed<lb/> please find check for &#36;125. being<lb/> the amount of donations collect<lb/>&#45;ed by me from the inmates of<lb/> our house&#44; in response to the<lb/> most eloquent appeal made by<lb/> you on Monday last in be&#45;<lb/>half of the Society of the &#34;United<lb/> Hebrew Charities&#34; of this city.<lb/></p>
            <p>By handing the same to<lb/> that useful society&#44; you will<lb/> greatly oblige<lb/></p>
            <p>Your sincere Friend<lb/>
                Clarence A. Hart.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
